A British climber has died after a fall during an ascent on Mt Olympus in northern Greece.Stephen Wright, 22, from Gloucestershire, was climbing with a 21-year-old Greek friend yesterday when he fell and sustained head injuries, police said. The pair were at an altitude of 700m (2,300ft).Rescue crews retrieved Wright's body shortly after 3am today.Mt Olympus is Greece's highest mountain at 2,917m (9,570ft). The mythological home of the Greek gods is a popular destination for climbers.